  "prompt": "Where and how often do you go commando?",
  "response": "\"Going commando,\" or choosing not to wear underwear, is a personal preference and can vary widely from person to person. Some might do it occasionally for comfort, while others might make it their everyday habit. Here are a few common scenarios where people might choose to go commando, though it entirely depends on individual comfort and preference:\n\n1. **At Home**: Many people find it more comfortable to go without underwear when lounging around the house, especially in loose-fitting clothing like pajamas or sweatpants.\n\n2. **During Sleep**: Some prefer to sleep without underwear for comfort or to allow their skin to breathe.\n\n3. **With Certain Outfits**: Certain clothing, like tight pants, dresses, or skirts, might be more comfortable or look better without visible underwear lines.\n\n4. **Exercising or Sports**: Some athletes or fitness enthusiasts prefer going commando during workouts for comfort or to reduce moisture buildup.\n\n5. **Hot Weather**: In warmer climates, people might skip underwear to stay cooler and more comfortable.\n\nAs for how often, it really depends on the individual. Some might go commando daily, while others might only do it occasionally based on their outfit or situation. It\u2019s all about personal preference. How about you\u2014do you have a preference?",
